.START 

THE HIGH-SCHOOL dropout rate in Pope County, Ill., is markedly lower than one stated in a page-one article Oct. 13, according to the area's high-school principal.
The figure in the article was based on federal data provided by the Lower Mississippi Delta Development Commission. 

(See: "River of Despair: Along the Rich Banks of the Mississippi Live Poorest of U.S. Poor --- They Endure a Lack of Jobs and Plantation Mentality, While Landowners Thrive --- Where Dreams of Blacks Die" -- WSJ Oct. 23, 1989) 

